            "id": "4580428",
            "title": "Kimberly-Clark leads all large-cap consumer staples stocks in YoY CapEx growth",
            "description": "<html><body><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\" data-eci=\"true\"><span>A rising capital expenditure figure often signals that a company is betting heavily on its own future growth. Below is a list of U.S. large-cap consumer staples stocks ranked by their year-over-year CapEx growth percentage, spanning multiple sectors and market capitalizations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">The list spans multiple sub-sectors, including Household Products, Tobacco, Consumer Staples Merchandise Retail, Agricultural Products &amp; Services, Food Retail, and Food Distributors.</p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Kimberly-Clark (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KMB\" title=\"Kimberly-Clark Corporation\">KMB</a>) tops the list with a CapEx growth rate of 57.84% year-over-year, as the company accelerates what it has called the largest transformation in its 150-year history under its \"Powering Care\" strategy, reinvesting aggressively in manufacturing capabilities and brand innovation after removing $200 million in structural costs through its 2024 restructuring program.</p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Altria Group (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MO\" title=\"Altria Group, Inc.\">MO</a>) and Target Corporation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TGT\" title=\"Target Corporation\">TGT</a>) follow in second and third place with growth rates of 52.11% and 28.92% respectively, while Bunge Global (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BG\" title=\"Bunge Global SA\">BG</a>) and Casey's General Stores (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CASY\" title=\"Casey's General Stores, Inc.\">CASY</a>) round out the top five at 25.22% and 23.72%, with Bunge projecting $1.5 to $1.7 billion in full-year capital expenditures for 2026 as it scales its global agri-processing operations.<span class=\"citation-nbsp\"></span><span class=\"citation inline\"></span></p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Procter &amp; Gamble (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PG\" title=\"The Procter &amp; Gamble Company\">PG</a>) and US Foods (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/USFD\" title=\"US Foods Holding Corp.\">USFD</a>) occupy the sixth and seventh positions with CapEx growth of 23.09% and 20.23% respectively, US Foods deploying $410 million in cash CapEx in fiscal 2025 as part of a plan to deploy over $4 billion in capital from 2025 to 2027.</p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">BJ's Wholesale Club (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BJ\" title=\"BJ's Wholesale Club Holdings, Inc.\">BJ</a>) and Costco (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COST\" title=\"Costco Wholesale Corporation\">COST</a>) follow at 19.40% and 17.30%, while Walmart (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WMT\" title=\"Walmart Inc.\">WMT</a>) rounds out the list at 12.02%. </p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Here is the list:</p>\n<ol class=\"marker:text-quiet list-decimal pl-8\">\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Kimberly-Clark Corporation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KMB\" title=\"Kimberly-Clark Corporation\">KMB</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 57.84%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Altria Group, Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MO\" title=\"Altria Group, Inc.\">MO</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 52.11%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Target Corporation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TGT\" title=\"Target Corporation\">TGT</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 28.92%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Bunge Global SA (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BG\" title=\"Bunge Global SA\">BG</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 25.22%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Casey's General Stores, Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CASY\" title=\"Casey's General Stores, Inc.\">CASY</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 23.72%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">The Procter &amp; Gamble Company (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PG\" title=\"The Procter &amp; Gamble Company\">PG</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 23.09%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">US Foods Holding Corp. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/USFD\" title=\"US Foods Holding Corp.\">USFD</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 20.23%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">BJ's Wholesale Club Holdings, Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BJ\" title=\"BJ's Wholesale Club Holdings, Inc.\">BJ</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 19.40%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Costco Wholesale Corporation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COST\" title=\"Costco Wholesale Corporation\">COST</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 17.30%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Walmart Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WMT\" title=\"Walmart Inc.\">WMT</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 12.02%</p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Consumer Staples ETFs: (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XLP\" title=\"State Street Consumer Staples Sel Sect SPDR ETF\">XLP</a></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/VDC\" title=\"Vanguard Consumer Staples Index Fund ETF\">VDC</a></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IYK\" title=\"iShares US Consumer Staples ETF\">IYK</a></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FSTA\" title=\"Fidelity MSCI Consumer Staples Index ETF\">FSTA</a></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KXI\" title=\"iShares Global Consumer Staples ETF\">KXI</a></span>), and (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/RSPS\" title=\"Invesco S&amp;P 500 Eql Wght Con Staples ETF\">RSPS</a></span>)</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
